parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front axle can cause damage to the front brake pad and caliper, and affect front-end alignment, leading to reduced vehicle safety and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Grinding noise from the front of the car
sound of something rolling around freely in the front driver-side wheel
broken axle pieces and nuts rolling around.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake wear and failure can lead to reduced stopping power, increased stopping distances, and accidents.
symptoms: Grinding or squeaking noises from the brakes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS brake malfunction can cause the brakes to lock up unexpectedly, leading to loss of control and accidents.
Brake pedal failure can cause the vehicle to continue moving even when the brakes are applied, leading to accidents.
symptoms: Clicking sound from the brake pedal
brake pedal jumping up and down
brake pedal going to the floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause loss of power, difficulty shifting gears, and sudden acceleration or deceleration, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Unintended shift into neutral can cause loss of power, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents, especially on high-speed roads.
symptoms: vehicle shifting into neutral while driving
fear of sudden lurching or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission shifting issues can cause loss of power, difficulty shifting gears, and sudden acceleration or deceleration, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Transmission shifting into neutral when brakes are applied

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Parking/reverse gear failure can cause unintended vehicle movement, leading to accidents or property damage.
symptoms: Vehicle rolling forward or backward when parked on an incline

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Speedometer failure can cause difficulty monitoring vehicle speed, leading to accidents or traffic violations.

A clogged catalytic converter can cause the engine to stall or run poorly, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing an accident. In extreme cases, it can also cause oil leaks and engine damage.
symptoms: the vehicle accelerates out of control
oil and smoke come from the engine compartment

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing an accident. It can also cause oil leaks and engine damage.
symptoms: the vehicle accelerates out of control
oil and smoke come from the engine compartment
a hole is blown through the engine.
